    "14420141": {
      "title": "Characterization of non-host resistance in broad bean to the wheat stripe rust pathogen",
      "abstract": "Background ::: Non-host resistance (NHR) confers plant species immunity against the majority of microbial pathogens and represents the most robust and durable form of plant resistance in nature. As one of the main genera of rust fungi with economic and biological importance, Puccinia infects almost all cereals but is unable to cause diseases on legumes. Little is known about the mechanism of this kind of effective defense in legumes to these non-host pathogens."
